.SH NAME
\fB²DPROG² \- Call list\fR: reads the call list of an AVM FRITZ!Box via TR-064 and records new calls in a MariaDB database
.br
(manpage-Hilfe in deutsch verfügbar: 'man ²DPROG²' oder 'man -Lde ²DPROG²')
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB²DPROG² [-<shortopt>|--<longopt> [<supplement>]] ...\fR
.SH SHORT DESCRIPTION
\fB²DPROG²\fR is a command line program that logs in to an AVM FRITZ!Box via the TR-064 protocol (service \fBX_AVM-DE_OnTel\fR, action \fBGetCallList\fR) and retrieves its call list.
.br
Each call (type, caller, called number, name, device, date, duration etc.) is checked and, if not yet present, inserted into a MariaDB database table.
.br
The program is suited for the regular, automated synchronisation of a FRITZ!Box's call list with a database, e.g. to display caller information in practice management software.
.SH INSTALLATION
.br
First, please read the chapters 'Functionality', 'Preconditions', 'Automatically installed software packages' and 'Implications' below. Then, if connected to the internet, call (e.g. by copying the line and pasting it into a terminal):
.br
\fBN=²DPROG²;P=${N}_inst.sh;cd ~;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/²gitv²/$N/master/install.sh -O$P&&sh $P\fR
.br
At last, call:
.br
 \fB²DPROG²\fR
.br
and answer some questions of the program, in particular the user name and password for accessing the FRITZ!Box (options \fB-fbusr\fR/\fB-fbpwd\fR).
.SH USAGE
Ideally, the program should have installed itself after the first call(s) and one-time answering of some questions in a self-running way.
.br
The program is typically called periodically via \fBcron\fR (option \fB-cm\fR/\fB--cronminutes\fR). At each call the complete call list delivered by the FRITZ!Box is processed; entries already present in the database table (default: \fBanrufe\fR), identified by type, date, name, number and duration, are skipped, new ones are inserted.
.br
\fB²DPROG² -listt\fR lists the most recently recorded entries including a success flag; the number of entries shown can be set with \fB-n\fR.
